title: In Time Of The Breaking Of Nations
creator: Thomas Hardy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 9 recordings of In Time Of "The Breaking Of Nations" by Thomas Hardy. This was the Weekly Poetry project for June 30, 2013. Written during the First World War, this is a poem about love, war and their timelessness by one of the best Victorian novelists. (Summary by Stav Nisser) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; poetry; adventure; nature; romance; war stories
